.TH "scmi_sensor_reading_get" 9 "scmi_sensor_reading_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scmi_sensor_reading_get \- Read scalar sensor value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scmi_sensor_reading_get
.BI "(const struct scmi_handle *handle "  ","
.BI "u32 sensor_id "  ","
.BI "u64 *value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "handle" 12
Platform handle
.IP "sensor_id" 12
Sensor ID
.IP "value" 12
The 64bit value sensor reading
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function returns a single 64 bit reading value representing the sensor
value; if the platform SCMI Protocol implementation and the sensor support
multiple axis and timestamped-reads, this just returns the first axis while
dropping the timestamp value.
Use instead the \fIscmi_sensor_reading_get_timestamped\fP to retrieve the array of
timestamped multi-axis values.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on Success
